`,y.jsx(t.p,{children:"Now I know one of my main points in my goals was not to be tied down to any provider yet here I am using both GitHub and Vercel however, I was more okay with this as obviously I'm just using git, and any static site provider which there will always be more."}),`
`,y.jsx(t.h3,{children:"General build"}),`
`,y.jsx(t.p,{children:"I do not claim to be a Docusaurus expert, so there are probably better ways to do parts of this."}),`
`,y.jsxs(t.p,{children:["For the most part, I followed the ",y.jsx(t.a,{href:"https://docusaurus.io/docs",children:"official tutorial"}),", then customized the favicon, colors, and homepage. I removed the default blog where it was not needed and used ",y.jsx(t.code,{children:".scss"})," instead of plain ",y.jsx(t.code,{children:".css"}),"."]}),`
